# VCF Migration Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and configure as needed

# =============================================================================
# PROXY CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# Deploy the proxies to IBM Code Engine and set the URLs here.
# This keeps your API key secure on the server side.

# Pricing Proxy - fetches live pricing from IBM Cloud Global Catalog
# See: functions/pricing-proxy/README.md for deployment instructions
VITE_PRICING_PROXY_URL=https://vcf-pricing-proxy.xxxx.us-south.codeengine.appdomain.cloud

# Profiles Proxy - fetches VPC/bare metal profiles and ROKS machine types
# See: functions/profiles-proxy/README.md for deployment instructions
VITE_PROFILES_PROXY_URL=https://vcf-profiles-proxy.xxxx.us-south.codeengine.appdomain.cloud

# =============================================================================
# AI PROXY CONFIGURATION (Optional)
# =============================================================================
# AI features use watsonx.ai via a Code Engine proxy.
# See: functions/ai-proxy/README.md for deployment instructions

# AI Proxy - provides classification, right-sizing, insights, and chat
VITE_AI_PROXY_URL=https://vcf-ai-proxy.xxxx.us-south.codeengine.appdomain.cloud

# =============================================================================
# PROXY SECURITY (CORS)
# =============================================================================
# All proxies use CORS origin restriction via the ALLOWED_ORIGINS env var
# set on the Code Engine app (not in this file). This replaces the old
# client-side API key approach.
#
# To configure on each proxy:
#   ibmcloud ce app update --name <proxy-name> \
#     --env ALLOWED_ORIGINS="https://your-frontend-url"
#
# Multiple origins can be comma-separated:
#   ALLOWED_ORIGINS="https://prod-url,http://localhost:5173"
#
# The ai-proxy also requires IBM_CLOUD_API_KEY (a service ID key, NOT your
# personal key) and WATSONX_PROJECT_ID set as env vars on the Code Engine app.

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
# - If proxies are not configured, the app uses static bundled data
# - Static data can be updated by running: npm run update-all
# - Proxies are recommended because they:
#   1. Keep credentials server-side (secure)
#   2. Cache responses to reduce API calls
#   3. Handle CORS issues automatically
#   4. Fall back gracefully if API is unavailable
